      ### Best Practices Checklist
    
      1. **‚úÖ Use permanent test wrapper files** - Never create temporary files
      2. **‚úÖ Consistent terminal sizing** - Use same dimensions across all tests
      3. **‚úÖ Generous timing** - Always allow sufficient time for app initialization
      4. **‚úÖ Absolute path resolution** - Use Path(__file__).parent patterns
      5. **‚úÖ Environment consistency** - Use isolated development environments
      6. **‚úÖ Meaningful test names** - Include screen/feature identifiers
      7. **‚úÖ Organized outputs** - Copy snapshots to well-structured directories
      8. **‚úÖ Documentation integration** - Auto-generate visual documentation
      9. **‚úÖ CI/CD compatibility** - Design for headless execution
      10. **‚úÖ Error scenario testing** - Test both success and failure states
    
      ### Troubleshooting Checklist
    
      When tests fail, verify:
      - [ ] gui_test_app.py is executable standalone
      - [ ] Import paths are correct in test wrapper
      - [ ] Sufficient wait time for system validation (minimum 3000ms)
      - [ ] Terminal size is consistent across tests
      - [ ] Using isolated development environment
      - [ ] Snapshot directories exist with proper permissions
      - [ ] Using absolute file paths
      - [ ] Test app path resolves correctly
    
